      • processAbstractionAtCall

        protected void processAbstractionAtCall​(MethodSummaries flows,
                                        AccessPath apAtCall,
                                        FlowSource source,
                                        soot.jimple.Stmt stmt,
                                        AccessPath sourceAP,
                                        boolean isAlias)
        Processes an abstraction at a method call. This is a partial summary that ends at a gap which can for instance be a callback into unknown code.
        Parameters:
        flows - The flows object to which to add the newly found flow
        apAtCall - The access path that has reached the method call
        source - The source at which the data flow started
        stmt - The statement at which the call happened
        sourceAP - The access path of the flow source
        isAlias - True if source and sink alias, otherwise false

      • createFlowSinkAtCall

        protected FlowSink createFlowSinkAtCall​(AccessPath apAtCall,
                                        GapDefinition gd,
                                        soot.jimple.Stmt stmt)
        Creates a flow sink at the given call site
        Parameters:
        apAtCall - The access path that arives at the given call site
        gd - The gap created at the given call site
        stmt - The statement containing the call site
        Returns:
        The flow sink created for the given access path at the given statement if it matches, otherwise false

      • processAbstractionAtReturn

        protected void processAbstractionAtReturn​(MethodSummaries flows,
                                          AccessPath apAtReturn,
                                          soot.SootMethod m,
                                          FlowSource source,
                                          soot.jimple.Stmt stmt,
                                          AccessPath sourceAP,
                                          boolean isAlias,
                                          boolean isInCallee)
        Processes an abstraction at the end of a method. This gives full summaries for the whole method
        Parameters:
        flows - The flows object to which to add the newly found flow
        apAtReturn - The access path that has reached the end of the method
        m - The method in which the flow has been found
        source - The source at which the data flow started
        stmt - The statement at which the flow left the method
        sourceAP - The access path of the flow source
        isAlias - True if source and sink alias, otherwise false
        isInCallee - True if the abstraction was recorded in a callee, false if it was recorded in the original method without any recursive calls or the like
